'''Ian David Bent''' (born January 1, 1938)<ref name="Grove">{{GroveOnline|title=Bent, Ian D.|author=Arnold Whitall|access-date=June 5, 2015}}</ref> is a British-born music scholar. He is now Professor Emeritus, after retiring from Full Professor of Music, at [[Columbia University]] and Honorary Professor in the History of [[music theory|Music Theory]] at the [[University of Cambridge]].<ref name="Columbia">"[http://music.columbia.edu/people/bios/ibent Bent, Ian (Emeritus)]", ''The Department of Music at Columbia University''.</ref><ref name="Cambridge">"[http://www.mus.cam.ac.uk/directory/ian-bent Faculty of Music: Ian Bent]", ''University of Cambridge''.</ref> 

He took the BA (1961), MusB (1962), and PhD (1969) all from the [[University of Cambridge]] before serving as a lecturer at [[King's College, London]] in 1965, a professor at the [[University of Nottingham]] in 1975, and Columbia University in 1986. His earliest research dealt with the early history of the English [[Chapel Royal]], but later he turned to the history of theory and analysis, and is now a historian of music theory.<ref name="Grove"/>

He is the editor (since 1991) of the ''Cambridge Studies in Music Theory and [[musical analysis|Analysis]]'' series and an area editor for the second edition of ''The New Grove Dictionary of Music''.<ref name="Columbia"/> {{As of|2011}}, he is the director of ''[[Heinrich Schenker|Schenker]] Documents Online''.<ref>"[http://mt.ccnmtl.columbia.edu/schenker/ Schenker Documents Online]", ''Columbia.edu''.</ref>

